I have these specifications for a shopping cart:

SPEC-001: GIVEN a logged-in user WHEN they add an item to the cart THEN the cart item count increases by 1.
SPEC-002: GIVEN a cart with items WHEN the user removes an item THEN the cart item count decreases by 1.
SPEC-003: GIVEN a cart with items WHEN the user changes quantity to 0 THEN the item is removed from the cart.
SPEC-004: GIVEN a cart WHEN the user adds an item already in the cart THEN the quantity increases instead of adding a duplicate.
SPEC-005: GIVEN an empty cart WHEN the user proceeds to checkout THEN they see an error message.

Here is the implementation:

```javascript
class Cart {
  constructor() { this.items = []; }

  addItem(product, quantity = 1) {
    const existing = this.items.find(i => i.product.id === product.id);
    if (existing) { existing.quantity += quantity; }
    else { this.items.push({ product, quantity }); }
  }

  removeItem(productId) {
    this.items = this.items.filter(i => i.product.id !== productId);
  }

  get itemCount() {
    return this.items.reduce((sum, i) => sum + i.quantity, 0);
  }
}
```

Verify the implementation against the specifications. Identify which specs are satisfied and which have gaps.
